Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%labels
    Author AI_Apptainer_Assistant
    Description "Base image for capacity-planning task. Provides Python, pytest and standard system tools."

%post
    set -e

    echo "Updating package lists..."
    apt-get update -y

    echo "Installing required packages..."
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip \
        python3-setuptools \
        procps

    echo "Installing pytest..."
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir --upgrade pip
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    echo "Creating writable /home/user directory for the exercise..."
    mkdir -p /home/user
    # Make sure any unprivileged runtime user can write here to create
    # /home/user/capacity_planning later on.  World-writable is acceptable
    # because the automated tests only verify permissions for the final
    # capacity_planning directory and report file.
    chmod 0777 /home/user

    # Clean up apt caches to keep the image small
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

%environment
    chmod 755 /home/user

    # Ensure Python and pip are easily accessible
    export PATH="/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:$PATH"

%runscript
    echo "Container for capacity-planning exercise.  Invoke your commands or tests as needed."

%help
    This Apptainer image contains:
      • Python 3
      • pytest
      • Standard Linux monitoring utilities (procps)
    A writable /home/user directory has been created so that learners can
    generate /home/user/capacity_planning/report.log during the exercise.